def news_search(keyword, displays, start):
    headers={"X-Naver-Client-Id":"jxx8ynlvrhua7CxtEIyz", 
             "X-Naver-Client-Secret":"n2ilChTs6S"}

    url="https://openapi.naver.com/v1/search/news.json?query=" + keyword  # book, blog, kin, news
    url=url+'&display='+ str(displays) + '&start='+ str(start)
    # print(url)
    res=requests.get(url, headers=headers)
    
    if res.status_code == 200:
        return res.json()
    else:
        return None

for i in range(1, 1000, 100):
    items = news_search(keyword, 100, i)['items']
    for j in items:
        title = j['title'].replace("&quot", "")
        link = j['link']
        date = j['pubDate']
        itemList.append([title, link, date])

In [6]:
news_content = []

for i in range(len(itemList)):
    paragraph = ""
    link = itemList[i][1]
    try:
        html = requests.get(link)
        soup = bs(html.content, 'html.parser')
        p_tmp = soup.find_all('p')
        for p in p_tmp:
            paragraph += p.text + "\n"
        news_content.append(paragraph)
    except:
        continue

news_text = ""

for text in news_content:
    news_text += text + "\n"
